reviews.review: Great show!  Sad that the series is coming to an end. Loved the identity struggles in the main characters.
Visually stunning in IMAX 3D. An understandable ending to a simple story set in a complicated universe. Great entertainment!
It was not original. It was just refried original trilogy.

An outstanding cast that completely made the action packed movie enjoyable from start to finish.  Filled with absolutely phenomenal special effects and dialogue, I would see it many times over and a must have when released on BluRay.

The story was fantastic and wrapped up this latest trilogy very well. Less awkward humor than the last one, which in my opinion is better. The two lead women in this movie are fantastic and the directors worked around Carrie's unfortunate death well. If you're a fan of Star Wars and have enjoyed the latest trilogy so far, you'll love it.

I grew up on the first Star Wars, which I'd say have earned an important place in film/art history, not to mention how it has affected culture, myself included. Having said that, this was my least favorite of all the Star Wars movies. The visuals and effects are always nice, but it rushes through the story irresponsibly and dismisses a lot of things that were built in the previous movies (even its own trilogy). Without wanting to give too much away, things all just seem to trivial, from hyperspace skipping, to overpowered force users, and obviously the First Order (what was the point of defeating the empire if it's only going to come back). There is too much emphasis on that, and not enough on the story or character development.
Aside from Star Wars, I like Abrams as a director, and I understand he had some big shoes to fill, but I think he should have allowed himself a little more freedom to tell a more original story. There's just too much concern with the franchise, and not enough with the plot.
Rogue One is an example of a great Star Wars film. It told an original story contained in the star wars universe that wasn't focused on the skywalkers (I mean, come on, in a universe that big there's only one family worthy of telling a story about?) or Jedis, and it was still great in its own way.
I understand Star Wars itself is sort of fantastic, but this is too much. Space fighters shouldn't emit smoke from thrusters, you can't take on a giant star destroyer on horses, and again, you can't just pull yourself out of a pickle by going into hyperspace (and if you can, why didn't we see this in the previous movies?). The whole thing seems like it was smashed together by kids.

The movie was wonderful and sad because you knew this was the end of this part of the story with the original cast. I stared crying when Princess Leia died and continued through the rest of the movie.
Loved it - great conclusion to the Star Wars series.  Has everything I want to see in a Star Wars movie

I don’t know what all the bad press has been.  The movie is freaking awesome.  Whether you are a casual fan or hardcore star wars (meaning you are 40-60 years old) you have to see this in the theater!  And the story is perfect, the acting is fantastic, and I can’t wait for the next movie!
It was awesome. The struggle between internal good and evil with good prevailing. I loved it.
